UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2220
1 AN ACT relating to cities.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 65.504 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) [Notwithstanding KRS 6.945, ]Beginning in the calendar year following the full
5 receipt of the initial funds statutorily required to be invested by private sector
6 investors, a consolidated local government, and the Commonwealth to the West
7 End Opportunity Partnership and continuing for twenty (20) years, eighty percent
8 (80%) of the incremental revenues shall be pledged to the West End Opportunity
9 Partnership by a consolidated local government and the Commonwealth.
10 (2) A local participation agreement shall be executed between the West End
11 Opportunity Partnership and the governing body involved in providing financing or
12 pledging incremental revenues to support the implementation of a development plan
13 in a development area.
14 (3) The local participation agreement shall be adopted by the governing body by
15 ordinance and shall include but not be limited to the following provisions:
16 (a) Identification of the parties to the local participation agreement and the duties
17 and responsibilities of each entity under the agreement;
18 (b) Specific identification of the incremental revenues released or pledged by type
19 of tax by each taxing district;
20 (c) The anticipated benefit to be received by each taxing district for the release or
21 pledge, including a detailed summary of old revenues collected;
22 (d) A requirement that pledged incremental revenues shall be accounted for
23 within a separate account under KRS 65.505;
24 (e) Terms of default and remedies, provided that no remedy shall permit the
25 withholding by any party to the local participation agreement of any
26 incremental revenues pledged to the special fund if increment bonds are
27 outstanding that are secured by a pledge of those incremental revenues;
Page 1 of 2
