UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2220
1 (f) The commencement date, activation date, and termination date; and
2 (g) Any other provisions not inconsistent with KRS 65.500 to 65.506.
3 (4) Any pledge of incremental revenues in a local participation agreement shall be
4 superior to any other pledge of revenues for any other purpose and shall, from the
5 activation date to the termination date set forth in the local participation agreement,
6 supersede any statute, ordinance, or resolution regarding the application or use of
7 incremental revenues. An ordinance in conflict with a local participation agreement
8 shall not be adopted while any increment bonds secured by that pledge remain
9 outstanding. Ordinances or resolutions pledging incremental revenues on a
10 subordinate basis to any existing pledges may be adopted.
11 (5) The local participation agreement established under this section and the
12 development area established under KRS 65.501 shall not be included in the
13 percentage calculation established by KRS 65.7049(2).
14 (6) Notwithstanding KRS 65.7049(2), the local participation agreement shall permit
15 residential property located within the development area to be eligible for
16 participation in a program granting property assessment or reassessment
17 moratoriums pursuant to KRS 99.600 when the incremental revenues related to that
18 residential property have not been pledged to support a tax increment financing
19 project established under KRS 65.490 to 65.499, 65.680 to 65.699, or 65.7041 to
20 65.7083 or an economic development project within the development area.
21 Section 2. The following KRS section is repealed:
22 6.945 Restriction of General Assembly's authority to require cities to make expenditures
23 or levy taxes.
